tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show mildly decreased fasting glucose and low total CO₂, which may suggest mild hypoglycemia and possible metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. HbA1c is at the upper end of normal, indicating good long-term glycemic control. Clinical correlation is recommended.
